🔷 🔥 Perfect Interview Answer

👉
Serialization in Java is the process of converting an object into a byte stream so it can be stored or
transmitted. It is achieved using the Serializable interface, and during deserialization, the object is
reconstructed without calling its constructor. Key concepts include serialVersionUID, transient fields,
and custom serialization methods.

🔷 Why static variables are NOT serialized

👉 Short answer:

Static variables belong to the class, not to the object — and serialization is only about object state.

🔷 Step-by-step understanding
🧠 1. What does serialization store?

When you serialize an object:

👉 JVM stores:

(i)  Object’s instance variables (fields)
(ii) Object-specific data

👉 It does NOT store class-level data